<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-2390] no close event when connection lost</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-2390</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;thrift nodejs lib (master)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no indication that connection lost if reconnect is not setup.&lt;br/&gt;
(There is no &quot;close&quot; event from connection object or RPC error callback)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;File: connection.js:167&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Connection.prototype.connection_gone = function () {&lt;br/&gt;
  var self = this;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  // If a retry is already in progress, just let that happen&lt;br/&gt;
  if (this.retry_timer || !this.max_attempts) &lt;/p&gt;
{
	 return;
  }&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Should be changed to &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Connection.prototype.connection_gone = function () {&lt;br/&gt;
  var self = this;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
  // If a retry is already in progress, just let that happen&lt;br/&gt;
  if (this.retry_timer) {	 return;  }

&lt;p&gt;  if(!this.max_attempts) &lt;/p&gt;
{
    self.emit(&quot;close&quot;);
    return;
  }</description>
